{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3747262,"name":"Clark Wang","username":"clarkw","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/e5b9ba/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-09-24T23:31:44.259Z","cooked":"<p>I am writing a command to align the robot with the reef using a Limelight. The command requires the drivetrain subsystem (a CommandSwerveDrivetrain) to move the robot to the desired location. I schedule this command with a Trigger to a button on the joystick, however upon testing the command runs its initialize() and skips directly to end() without running execute() or isFinished().</p>
<p>I assume something is interrupting the command the moment it is being triggered. The problem is, I don’t know what. The drivetrain has a default command (from drivetrain.applyRequest()), however I can’t see how that would be the problem since triggering my reef align command would temporarily cancel the default command. What’s even more perplexing is that I could run the command perfectly fine from the SmartDashboard, but not with a trigger.</p>
<p>Here are some snippets of my code:</p>
<p>Reef Align Command:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">package frc.robot.commands;

import com.ctre.phoenix6.swerve.SwerveRequest;

import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.Command;
import edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Pose3d;
import edu.wpi.first.math.kinematics.ChassisSpeeds;
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.CommandScheduler;
import frc.robot.Camera;

import frc.robot.LimelightHelpers;
import frc.robot.LimelightConstants;
import frc.robot.subsystems.CommandSwerveDrivetrain;

public class alignReefLeft extends Command {
    CommandSwerveDrivetrain drivetrain;
    public alignReefLeft(CommandSwerveDrivetrain drivetrain){
        this.drivetrain = drivetrain;
        addRequirements(this.drivetrain);
    }

    @Override
    public void initialize(){
        System.out.println("Aligning!");
    }

    @Override
    public void execute(){
        System.out.println("Executing!");
        Camera.updateCurrentPose();
        // Pose3d botPose = Camera.getCurrentPose();

        if(Camera.checkIfTag()){
            System.out.println("Got tag!");
            this.drivetrain.driveRobotRelative(new ChassisSpeeds(Camera.getXOutput(), Camera.getYOutput(), Camera.getRotOutput()));
        }
    }

    @Override
    public void end(boolean interrupted){
        System.out.println("Aligned!, " + interrupted);
        this.drivetrain.driveRobotRelative(new ChassisSpeeds(0, 0, 0));
    }

    @Override
    public boolean isFinished(){
        System.out.println(Camera.checkAligned());
        return Camera.checkAligned();
    }

}

</code></pre>
